But her country had called, and she would not repine, Though costly the sacrifice placed on its shrine;
41 All prisoners had been released from Camp Douglas by at least July 5, 1865. Official Records, Ser. II, Vol. VIII, 700-701. As of May 31 there were still 4,136 prisoners at Douglas; 4,090 were released in June. Ibid., 1002.
Her hearts dearest hopes on its after [altar] she lay, When she sent out her boy, in the jacket of gray.
